article.headline: Murray St. 63, Jacksonville St. 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Bruce Carter scored the game-winning points with 26 seconds left on the clock to boost Murray State to a 63-61 win over Jacksonville State Saturday night. It was a hard-fought victory for the Racers (10-5, 12-11 Ohio Valley Conference), who struggled through a first half plagued with 11 turnovers. George Ray led Murray State with 16 points while Shawn Witherspoon added 15 and Carter followed with 13. Jacksonville St. (6-18, 4-11) led 31-28 at the half after shooting 38.7 percent from the field. Courtney Bradley led all scorers with 23 points and Nick Smith added 16 to round out the double-digit scoring for the Gamecocks. Murray State built a 48-42 lead after a 20-11 run in the second. JSU battled back to three points with 4:00 left and tied the game on a long three-pointer by Bradley to make it 59-59. After a MSU turnover, the Gamecocks took a two point lead with 2:30 left on a rebound by Erik Adams. The Racers tied the score at 61-61 with 2:02 left on a short jumper by Witherspoon and Carter scored win the game.
